A good understanding in reaction mechanisms and catalyst active sites is very important to guide the design the OER electrocatalysts. In alkaline water electrolysis, OER is the half-reaction that occurs at the anode. Different reaction mechanisms have been suggested, of which the most widely agreed mechanism is known as the conventional adsorbate evolution mechanism [16], which is described by Eqs. (1)–(4) [17].1M+OH-→MOH+e-,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
