When the pH of the deposition is not adjusted, the solution was slightly acidic (~ 4.2), which was ascribed to the presence of nickel sulphate, that formed an acidic aqueous solution with pH 4.5. During the deposition process under this pH, the dominating reaction occurring in electrode/electrolyte interphase was the reduction of water:H2O+e-→12H2+OH-E0=-0.83V.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
